1
00:00:06,533 --> 00:00:09,767
[Chu Tae Jeong]

2
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:12,167
Tae Jeong is a cop.

3
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,333
You can never escape him.

4
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:06,800
<i>You spared Chu Tae Jeong
just because he's a cop?</i>

5
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:10,333
Luckily, I found out right before
the execution and stopped immediately.

6
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,700
<i>Things are getting annoyingly complicated.</i>

7
00:01:13,567 --> 00:01:18,833
<i>Are you sure he really thinks
you're Heo Dong Hwa's brother?</i>

8
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,533
Yes, I'm sure.

9
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:26,133
It's been so long since he saw him
that he doesn't remember his face.

10
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:29,867
<i>Then keep pretending to be Heo Dong Jin
and let him go without him noticing.</i>

11
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:34,233
<i>You need to get this job done flawlessly</i>

12
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:36,933
<i>if you want to be heard, don't you think?</i>

13
00:02:17,133 --> 00:02:19,633
<i>Are you really going down to Dongcheon?</i>

14
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:22,967
<i>That case closed ten years ago.
The evidence was solid.</i>

15
00:02:22,967 --> 00:02:26,067
<i>Your father's car was found in the reservoir.</i>

16
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:35,264
[Reservoir]

17
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:10,400
<i>How did I fall into such a deep sleep?</i>

18
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,967
You're awake?

19
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:22,800
Are you going to have breakfast?

20
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,267
Want some too?

21
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:30,267
Sure, I'll go wash up quickly.

22
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:41,200
By the way, Dong Jin.

23
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,667
Did Dong Hwa call you?

24
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,700
It's like he's dead, you know?

25
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:56,733
Did you sleep well?

26
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:00,500
You look tired.

27
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:03,800
It must've been chilly last night
without a blanket.

28
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:07,233
Right, the blanket.

29
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:08,933
Thanks.

30
00:04:10,267 --> 00:04:12,900
You must've felt inconvenienced yesterday
because of me, right?

31
00:04:18,533 --> 00:04:20,267
No, not really.

32
00:04:20,267 --> 00:04:24,300
I'll just leave if we don't hear
from Dong Hwa by this evening.

33
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:30,733
What's that sound?

34
00:04:36,367 --> 00:04:38,700
It sounds like it's coming
from outside, right?

35
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:42,500
Outside?

36
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,767
Doesn't it sound like it's coming from below?

37
00:04:44,767 --> 00:04:46,267
Is there a basement in this house?

38
00:04:46,267 --> 00:04:47,800
The ventilation fan is acting up.

39
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:51,500
It keeps making weird noise as it spins.

40
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,500
Where is the ventilation fan?

41
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,900
Sounds like it needs fixing?

42
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:55,900
I'll help you.

43
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,633
It's fine.

44
00:04:58,933 --> 00:05:02,267
I can take care of it myself.

45
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:06,033
Dong Jin, let me return the favor
at least for letting me stay.

46
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,133
Can you see inside the fan?

47
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:13,767
They say usually something gets stuck between
the filter and the motor, causing the noise.

48
00:05:13,767 --> 00:05:16,033
Oh, is that right?

49
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:22,467
I heard they're building
a resort in Dongcheon.

50
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:25,833
They're leveling the mountain over there
to build a golf course.

51
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:28,467
The population here will grow, right?

52
00:05:28,467 --> 00:05:30,767
Is that why you got assigned
to Dongcheon Police Station?

53
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:32,800
No, I volunteered.

54
00:05:33,567 --> 00:05:37,920
- But how did you know I'm a cop?
- Well...

55
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:42,267
I saw the uniform in your closet.

56
00:05:43,967 --> 00:05:45,933
Why did you volunteer?

57
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:51,167
My father was a detective
in Dongcheon's violent crimes unit.

58
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:54,933
I want to follow in his footsteps.

59
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,033
Is he retired now?

60
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:03,367
He passed away ten years ago.

61
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:06,467
He committed suicide.

62
00:06:08,167 --> 00:06:10,333
I'm sorry.

63
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,133
It's okay.

64
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:14,467
Actually, I don't believe it.

65
00:06:14,467 --> 00:06:18,467
My father wasn't the type to
make such a choice, leaving me behind.

66
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:20,600
That's why I came.

67
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:25,067
I want to know what happened
before Dongcheon changes.

68
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,600
How can you be so sure?

69
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:36,433
The day after my father passed
was my birthday.

70
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:39,167
He had even reserved a restaurant
for us to have dinner together.

71
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:41,633
He wouldn't have made that kind of choice.

72
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:46,600
Didn't you tell this to the police
investigating the case back then?

73
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,333
I did.

74
00:06:48,967 --> 00:06:53,233
No matter how much I said
it was strange, no one would listen.

75
00:06:53,233 --> 00:06:55,300
They said the evidence was clear.

76
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:59,033
I brought up
such a heavy topic out of nowhere.

77
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:01,300
I must've felt very comfortable with you.

78
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,100
Investigate it thoroughly.

79
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,933
Huh?

80
00:07:10,667 --> 00:07:13,200
You said it's important to you.

81
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:19,967
Why do you smile like that?

82
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:24,933
Actually, you're the first person
who's ever said that to me.

83
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,900
Thank you.

84
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:34,767
Go wash up now.
I'll clean up and head back in.

85
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:36,467
Okay.

86
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,133
"Final past due notice"?

87
00:08:03,133 --> 00:08:06,667
[Final Past Due Notice from Jungjin Bank]
Where on earth is Dong Hwa?

88
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:22,267
This isn't why I gave you that.

89
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:24,467
I guess you're not hungry enough.

90
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:31,633
Is Tae Jeong still alive?

91
00:08:31,633 --> 00:08:34,467
I told you to answer my questions, didn't I?

92
00:08:34,467 --> 00:08:36,733
So he's still alive, isn't he?

93
00:08:36,733 --> 00:08:39,733
How come? You should've locked him up too.

94
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:42,233
You can't harm him because he's too cute?

95
00:08:45,467 --> 00:08:47,967
That's none of your business.

96
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:53,067
Do you really think Chu Tae Jeong
isn't suspicious of you at all?

97
00:08:53,067 --> 00:08:55,567
You're a stranger
staying at his friend's house.

98
00:08:56,367 --> 00:09:01,033
Hey, stop talking nonsense.

99
00:09:01,033 --> 00:09:03,133
Tell me where the cell phone is.

100
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:08,867
If I tell you, then what?

101
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:13,867
Try me.

102
00:09:15,167 --> 00:09:17,633
Let me have a smoke too.

103
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:21,167
A smoke?

104
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:25,633
You're dangling it in front of me.
It's driving me crazy that I can't have one.

105
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:30,700
If I let you, then what?

106
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:42,867
If I tell you,
you'll spare my life at least, right?

107
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:47,500
Make up your mind by today.

108
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:16,433
Where did you go?

109
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:19,667
I had some quick errands to run.

110
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:23,567
Dong Jin, you don't like loud noises, right?

111
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:25,533
It's okay.

112
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:27,267
Play it.

113
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,400
What are you making?

114
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,733
Let's have dinner together.

115
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:38,433
I actually brought it for Dong Hwa.

116
00:10:38,433 --> 00:10:40,833
Dong Jin, do you like shrimp?

117
00:10:40,833 --> 00:10:42,533
Huh?

118
00:10:44,267 --> 00:10:47,600
Not sure. I've never tried it.

119
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,933
What?

120
00:10:48,933 --> 00:10:51,767
But Dong Hwa loves shrimp, you know?

121
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:54,700
That's so odd. How is that possible?

122
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:01,200
How is it?

123
00:11:01,967 --> 00:11:04,100
It's good.

124
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,167
Isn't it?

125
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:08,867
I've made pasta like a thousand times.

126
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:10,567
How come?

127
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,067
Because I spend a lot of time alone.

128
00:11:14,067 --> 00:11:19,267
When you're alone, instant noodles or pasta
is the easiest to make.

129
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:23,367
You wouldn't know the loneliness
of eating alone, would you?

130
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:25,567
I do.

131
00:11:25,567 --> 00:11:28,067
How do you know?

132
00:11:28,067 --> 00:11:32,567
When I was young,
I spent a lot of time alone too.

133
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:37,200
What did you usually do when you were alone?

134
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,967
I exercised.

135
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:44,467
Repeating the same routine every day.

136
00:11:44,467 --> 00:11:47,267
Did you draw those around that time too?

137
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:48,633
What?

138
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:50,433
Actually, I looked through your sketchbook.

139
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:53,100
You're really good at drawing.

140
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:55,367
Have you ever taken lessons?

141
00:11:55,367 --> 00:11:58,467
It's just a hobby I do on my own.

142
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:02,833
Then why not take proper art lessons?

143
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:05,700
Your skills are too good
to waste as just a hobby.

144
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:09,500
That sort of thing doesn't suit me.

145
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,867
I've been told that a lot too.

146
00:12:19,867 --> 00:12:21,267
"Can someone like you really be a detective?"

147
00:12:21,267 --> 00:12:23,067
"Aren't you just going to
get caught by criminals?"

148
00:12:23,067 --> 00:12:25,233
Things like that.

149
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:29,167
But I think you really have talent.

150
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:32,167
Even though I don't know much about art,

151
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:35,000
I sensed that as soon as I saw your drawings.

152
00:12:36,233 --> 00:12:38,233
It's not that good.

153
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,100
I especially like your ocean drawings.

154
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,800
Where is it?

155
00:12:44,733 --> 00:12:46,100
Faroe Islands.

156
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:48,067
Have you been there?

157
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:51,967
They are islands in Northern Europe.

158
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:54,033
I just drew them from a photo.

159
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:57,500
Then why don't you go see them
for yourself sometime?

160
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,833
Why would I go there?

161
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:02,767
Just to draw?

162
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:05,333
What do you mean, "just to draw"?

163
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:07,567
I'll buy that drawing from you.

164
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:09,600
Before its value goes up.

165
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,567
You're exaggerating.

166
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,800
I talked too much, didn't I?

167
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:22,633
At least you know.

168
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:33,867
It was nice to see you again, Dong Jin.

169
00:13:45,667 --> 00:13:47,833
Dong Jin!

170
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:49,667
I'm going now.

171
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:54,533
Are you already asleep?

172
00:13:57,300 --> 00:14:01,000
Dong Jin, say hi to Dong Hwa for me.

173
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,233
Dong Jin?

174
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,933
Are you asleep?

175
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:09,100
Dong Jin.

176
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,467
Are you not feeling well?

177
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:18,067
You have a fever.

178
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:22,433
Are you allergic to shrimp?

179
00:14:22,433 --> 00:14:25,067
So you really hadn't tried it before.

180
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:27,600
This isn't good.
Let me get you to the hospital.

181
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,767
No, not the hospital.

182
00:14:30,767 --> 00:14:34,233
What do you mean? Look at your condition.

183
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:36,533
I said no.

184
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:39,100
I'll be fine after a little rest.

185
00:14:41,567 --> 00:14:43,867
I'm calling 911.

186
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:51,133
Jeez, good grief.

187
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,000
Dong Jin.

188
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,500
Dong Jin, I'm sorry.

189
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,700
I didn't know you were allergic.

190
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:04,133
But... it was delicious.

191
00:17:25,533 --> 00:17:29,067
<i>You were sleeping so deeply
so I didn't want to wake you up.</i>

192
00:17:29,067 --> 00:17:31,800
<i>I think me being here
was inconveniencing you,</i>

193
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,367
<i>so I'm leaving without saying goodbye.</i>

194
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:36,133
<i>It was fun even though it was a short time.</i>

195
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:45,567
<i>How could he leave without saying goodbye?</i>

196
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,767
It does look amazing indeed.

197
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:18,967
So it is you, Chu Tae Jeong.

198
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:22,933
Chul Jin? Are you on duty?

199
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:25,867
Yeah. Hey, if you're here,
you should've called me, man.

200
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:28,500
I'm your senior at work now.

201
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:32,167
Sorry, I've been out of it.

202
00:18:32,167 --> 00:18:34,000
I was kidding, you punk.

203
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,633
Jeez, you're still so uptight.

204
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:39,800
How will you survive at work?

205
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,133
Where are you staying now?

206
00:18:41,133 --> 00:18:43,733
At a motel in town.

207
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:45,600
Rough times.

208
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:49,600
The dorm will be fixed soon,
so hang in there for a few more days.

209
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:53,967
The Seoul office didn't make a fuss
about you coming here?

210
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:55,967
Not really.

211
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:57,767
Even if they did, it is what it is.

212
00:18:57,767 --> 00:18:59,633
You're right.

213
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:03,533
I put in a good word for you with our chief.

214
00:19:03,533 --> 00:19:07,967
I told him you were my buddy from home
who's super smart.

215
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:09,800
Thanks.

216
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:15,100
Anyway, I was already planning to bring it up
when we met.

217
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:19,733
You can't just stir things up here
like you did in Seoul.

218
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:22,000
Don't mess around, got it?

219
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:26,700
What did I stir up?

220
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,733
I was just investigating a case
that needed to be looked into.

221
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:30,833
Tae Jeong.

222
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:33,900
Don't you know
what kind of place my hometown is?

223
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:36,967
It's quiet, isn't it?

224
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:39,008
People are living peacefully here.

225
00:19:39,008 --> 00:19:40,333
Don't go poking around for no reason

226
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:43,000
and drive down the land prices.

227
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:46,500
Just do what you're told.

228
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,867
I can take care of myself.

229
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:53,472
Your business becomes my business.

230
00:19:53,472 --> 00:19:56,267
That's why I'm telling you this, you punk.

231
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:02,100
By the way, since you got here,
you've been staying at the motel?

232
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:06,467
No, I was at Dong Hwa's place.

233
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:09,000
But where on earth
did that punk disappear to?

234
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,667
I haven't heard from him.

235
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:13,800
You're right. He hasn't answered
my calls either, you know?

236
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:30,200
So you were alone at Dong Hwa's place?

237
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,200
No.

238
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,267
I was with Dong Jin.

239
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:39,100
<i>Who?</i>

240
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:41,433
<i>Dong Hwa's brother.</i>

241
00:20:41,433 --> 00:20:42,567
Heo Dong Jin.

242
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:46,567
Darn you, why are you
playing such a sick joke?

243
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:49,800
What are you talking about?

244
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:52,467
Jeez, you're a lunatic.

245
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:54,733
Dong Jin died last year.

246
00:20:54,733 --> 00:20:57,200
You've gone too far
with your jokes, you punk.

247
00:20:57,200 --> 00:21:00,600
Don't you know
Dong Hwa's still messed up over that?

248
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,633
Did you see a ghost or something?

249
00:21:07,633 --> 00:21:10,133
Who were you staying with?

